**Core Implementation in `tabs/state.rs` and `editor/undo.rs`:**

1. **Extend Tab struct with undo/redo stacks:**
   ```rust
   struct Tab {
       // existing fields...
       undo_stack: Vec<UndoEntry>,
       redo_stack: Vec<UndoEntry>,
       max_history: usize, // 100
       last_saved_content: String,
   }

   #[derive(Clone)]
   enum UndoEntry {
       Insert { pos: usize, text: String },
       Delete { pos: usize, text: String },
       Replace { pos: usize, old: String, new: String },
   }
   ```

2. **Smart change detection at word/line boundaries:**
   - Capture changes only on word completion (space/enter), backspace to word boundary, or explicit actions (paste/cut)
   - Compare current content vs previous snapshot using diff algorithm (simple LCS or word-boundary diff)
   - Store minimal delta: `{pos, old_text, new_text}`

3. **Undo/Redo methods on Tab:**
   ```rust
   impl Tab {
       fn push_undo(&mut self, entry: UndoEntry) {
           self.undo_stack.push(entry);
           self.redo_stack.clear(); // Clear redo on new action
           if self.undo_stack.len() > self.max_history {
               self.undo_stack.remove(0);
           }
       }

       fn undo(&mut self) -> bool {
           if let Some(entry) = self.undo_stack.pop() {
               self.redo_stack.push(entry.clone());
               // Apply inverse operation
               match entry {
                   UndoEntry::Insert { pos, text } => {
                       self.content.replace_range(pos..pos+text.len(), "");
                   }
                   // ... other cases
               }
               true
           } else { false }
       }
   }
   ```

4. **Keyboard shortcuts in `ui/shortcuts.rs`:**
   - `Ctrl+Z`: `tab_manager.active_tab_mut().unwrap().undo()`
   - `Ctrl+Y` / `Ctrl+Shift+Z`: `redo()`
   - Clear redo stack on new input

5. **UI Integration:**
   - Add undo/redo buttons to toolbar/ribbon: `ui.button("↶").clicked() => app.undo()`
   - Toast notification: `if performed { ui.label("Undone").highlight(); }`

6. **Edge cases & persistence:**
   - Empty stacks: no-op with visual feedback
   - Tab switching: maintain per-tab stacks
   - Save: `last_saved_content = content.clone(); undo_stack.clear();`
   - WYSIWYG mode: sync source changes to rendered view

